5:
That Suizen brat... Why's he gotta
push all the annoying jobs on us?
8:
Does he seriously think we're gonna
find a town hidden by a barrier this
far into the mountains?
11:
That's what the rumors say. It is our
job to determine whether this is fact
or fiction—
18:
There's a barrier up ahead that
repels yokai. I implore you to retrea—
22:
Oh... Oh my goodness! Are you a
yokai?
26:
...Neither I nor Nimbus here are
yokai. Could you please calm down
and give us a chance to explain?
30:
Huh?! N-now that you mention it... I
do not sense the same spiritual
energy I find in yokai...
33: In that case... State your business.
37:
Uh... Cold much? Shouldn't you be
relieved that we're NOT yokai?
43:
We're here at the request of the
Diviners' Commission. We've been
sent to investigate rumors of a town
hidden—
54: Oh no! We have to help—
67: Oh! I'm so glad you're all right!
73:
No need to thank me. I'm just glad I
moved when I did... This little guy is a
friend of yours, right?
77:
Please forgive my rude behavior
earlier. Allow me to introduce myself.
82:
I am Maihime Amenohara. My
family is the one maintaining the
barrier around my village.
87:
So the village and barrier are both
real...
91:
You said the barrier keeps yokai out,
right? So why are you friends with
this yokai?
99:
I see... So your mother was the one
to erect the barrier.
103:
That's right... She set it up after the
village was attacked, and it's been
there ever since...
105:
We don't have any contact with the
outside world, so all the villagers
consider yokai to be an evil
existence and fear them.
114:
That's right! Who could possibly
hate such adorable, brave creatures?
119:
Yes, well... I suppose they could be
considered adorable by some
people.
123: She's right. This yokai is very cute.
128:
Aren't they?! Oh, I just want to
squeeze them all day! Their fur feels
incredibly soft, like the finest silk
you've ever felt in your—
132:
Ah! M-my apologies! I just got
carried away...
138:
You have nothing to apologize for.
But getting back to our
investigation...
141:
Ah, that's right. There should be no
problem with you continuing your
work.
144:
However, the villagers deeply fear
the outside world... So I ask that you
remain hidden.
147:
Understood. We do not wish to
frighten the residents here either.
151:
But how are we going to investigate
without getting caught by the
villagers?
155:
Please leave that to me. I shall be
your guide.
157:
After all, I've been leaving the barrier
in secret for a long time now.
161:
Haha... So we're not the only ones
sneaking around.
166:
That's right, and I'd like to say I'm
quite skilled at it. After all, I cannot
have anyone finding out about my
own ventures outside.
169:
Um... I-in return for being your
guide... W-would you...
173:
Would you please become friends
with me?!
177:
I would love to hear more about the
outside world and yokai!
183: Of course. Let's be friends, Maihime.
188:
Sounds good to me. Here's to a long
friendship.
191: Oh, thank you! Thank you so much!
196:
Oh... I've always wanted friends I
could discuss yokai with.
200:
Uh... Does she think we're all yokai
fanatics like her?
203:
Come on, what's the harm? I'm sure
Inaho and the others will be happy
to hear this.
208:
Now then, let the yokai fan club
meeting begin!
